<br />
I'd be very thankful if you do it.
<br />

<br />
Actually, phpBBHacks.com has Links Rejector (LR) under the name of just &quot;bbAntiSpam&quot;: <a href="http://phpbbhacks.com/download/6643" target="_blank" class="postlink">http://phpbbhacks.com/download/6643</a>. And I'm in doubt what to do. On the one side, I consider LR to be a failed experiment. On the other side, on one of my forums, LR works perfectly as a good protection against human spammers.
<br />

<br />
As for TC, I submitted this MOD to the phpBBHacks.com database, but it wasn't accepted. I don't know why, and I consider it's too bad for community. Please help, if you can! The description can be taken from here: <a href="http://www.phpbb.com/phpBB/viewtopic.php?t=472940" target="_blank" class="postlink">http://www.phpbb.com/phpBB/viewtopic.php?t=472940</a>. The latest version is 1.0.7, the version on phpbb.com is 1.0.1, but it's not important: the code is the same. I was incrementing the version number each time I added a new language file. Now all the language files are put to the language pack: <a href="http://bbantispam.com/tc/tc_langpack.zip" target="_blank" class="postlink">http://bbantispam.com/tc/tc_langpack.zip</a>.
<br />

<br />
Also I wonder if it's reasonable to submit Advanced Textual Confirmation for phpBB3. Here is the discussion on phpbb.com: <a href="http://www.phpbb.com/community/viewtopic.php?f=70&amp;t=544007" target="_blank" class="postlink">http://www.phpbb.com/community/viewtopic.php?f=70&amp;t=544007</a>.<br />_________________<br />Oleg Parashchenko, bbAntiSpam
